  "title" : "Get client&#39;s browser name and ip address using Spring",
  "body" : "<p>I'm trying to get a list of all online users. I'm planning to do so, using SpringRegistry. But i also have to get user's browser info and ip address. I know that i could do it in javascript, but i need to retrieve all user's details, not only current one's. </p>\n\n<p><strong>EDIT</strong></p>\n\n<p>Here's my code:</p>\n\n<pre><code> @GetMapping(\"/\")\n public String index(HttpServletRequest request){\n String ip=request.getRemoteAddr(); // \"0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1\"\n return \"index\";\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
